, \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Subways\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Subways\"}, {\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8825700713373036e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The distinction\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"the first woman\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual Olympic champion\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"Ealing\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's singles\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1900 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cooper defeated the French champion, Helene Prevost in straight sets and then won a second gold medal in the mixed doubles with Reggie Doherty.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9660712446651613, \"rank\": 0.03399105476956977, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pr\\u00e9vost_Car\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Prevost\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pr\\u00e9vost_Car\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pr\\u00e9vost_Car\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cooper\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"straight sets\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"a second gold medal\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed doubles\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"Reggie Doherty\", \"from\":